Month = {JAN},
Abstract = {Research on identity has been a growing domain in the contexts of
   teacher education and mathematics education; however, identity work has
   been explored to a much lesser extent, with a future orientation
   overlooked. In addition, earlier studies have not provided sufficient
   knowledge on how different elementary teacher education programs might
   facilitate pre-service teachers' identity work. In this study, we
   compare future-oriented mathematical identity work through a narrative
   framework considering six pre-service teachers undergoing two different
   teacher education programs. All pre-service teachers reported having had
   negative experiences with mathematics during their school years. Based
   on the results we conclude that despite the striking similarities in
   pre-service teachers' mathematical backgrounds, the ways in which these
   cases are conducting their identity work differ substantially. It seems
   that the main reasons for these differences are different emphases and
   pedagogical practices in mathematics education courses. Additionally, we
   further elaborate on our earlier conceptualisation of identity work.},
