Abstract = {In this paper, we offer a comparative review of research on
   understanding and promoting students' mathematical thinking. The sources
   for the review are papers that were published in Educational Studies in
   Mathematics (ESM) during two windows of time: 1994-1998 and 2014-2018.
   Selection of these two time periods enables us to comment on the ``state
   of the art{''} in research as well as identify changes over the past 25
   years. The review is guided by an analysis of conceptualizations of
   ``mathematical thinking{''} proposed in the research literature,
   selected curriculum documents, and international assessment programs
   such as the OECD's Programme for International Student Assessment
   (PISA). The review not only documents salient features of research
   studies, such as the country of origin of the authors, educational level
   of the participants, research aims, theoretical perspectives, and
   methodological approaches, but also identifies the contribution to
   knowledge made by this body of work as well as future research
   directions and opportunities.},
