Month = {FEB},
Abstract = {In our exploration of the order of operations we focus on the following
   claim: ``In the conventional order of operations, division should be
   performed before multiplication.{''} This initially surprising claim is
   based on the acronym BEDMAS, a popular mnemonic used in Canada to assist
   students in remembering the order of operations. The claim was voiced by
   a teacher and then presented for consideration to a class of prospective
   elementary school teachers. We investigate the participants'
   understanding of the order of operations, focusing on the operations of
   multiplication and division. We report on participants' ways of
   resolving a cognitive conflict faced as a result of relying on memorized
   mnemonics.},
