Month = {MAY},
Abstract = {Free, open, online, calculus forums are websites where students from
   around the world can post course-related queries that may be viewed and
   responded to by anonymous others. These sites are an emergent resource
   for students seeking help and have become a part of many students'
   mathematical experience. The purpose of this paper is to introduce and
   describe the forums to the research community as a computer-mediated
   form of help seeking, and to briefly characterize the forms of student
   activity in one popular calculus help forum. Two hundred exchanges on
   limit and related rates were collected and examined for evidence that
   students are contributing ideas and proposals for action when they
   initiate the exchange and following intervention. The findings justify
   the need for further research since students are using the forums in a
   variety of ways and sometimes participate meaningfully. The forums have
   potential for testing student responses to pedagogical approaches.},
