Abstract = {In this paper, we consider gestures as part of the resources activated
   in the mathematics classroom: speech, inscriptions, artifacts, etc. As
   such, gestures are seen as one of the semiotic tools used by students
   and teacher in mathematics teaching-learning. To analyze them, we
